] and YNW Melly)}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2019\n| ''[[Long Live Mexico]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | \"Young Grizzley World\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/tee-grizzley-taps-ynw-melly-and-a-boogie-wit-da-hoodie-for-young-grizzley-world-new-song.1983282.html|title=Tee Grizzley Taps YNW Melly & A Boogie Wit Da Hoodie For \"Young Grizzley World\"|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2019-07-23}}</ref><br/>{{small|([[Tee Grizzley]] featuring [[A Boogie wit da Hoodie]] and YNW Melly)}}\n|''[[Scriptures (album)|Scriptures]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" |\"100 Shells\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/ynw-melly-hops-on-yung-bans-new-song-100-shells-new-song.1983896.html|title=YNW Melly Hops On Yung Bans' New Song \"100 Shells\"|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2019-08-02}}</ref><br/>{{small|([[Yung Bans]] featuring YNW Melly)}}\n|''[[Misunderstood (album)|Misunderstood]]''\n|}\n\n===Other charted songs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard Hot 100|US]]<br /><ref name=\"Hot 100\"/>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US R&B/HH]]<br /><ref name=\"R&B/Hip-Hop\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Kanye-West/chart-history/r-b-hip-hop-songs|title=Kayne West Chart history|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 26, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"R&B/Hip-Hop2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ynw-melly/chart-history/BSI|title=YNW Melly R&B/Hip-Hop Songs Chart history|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 27, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Hot 100|CAN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ynw-melly/chart-history/canadian-hot-100|title=YNW Melly Chart History: Canadian Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 24, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[VG-lista|NOR]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vglista.no/topplister/topp-20-single-2020-05/|title=VG-lista \u2013 Topp 20 Single uke 5, 2020|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Official New Zealand Music Chart|NZ<br />Hot]]<br /><ref>Peaks on the NZ Hot Singles Chart:\n* \"Suicidal\": {{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4797|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=December 30, 2019|accessdate=December 28, 2019}}\n* \"6 Kiss\" and \"Bang Bang\": {{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4784|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|date=December 2, 2019|accessdate=November 30, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Sverigetopplistan|SWE]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/41?dspy=2020&dspp=5|title=Veckolista Singlar, vecka 5|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=February 1, 2020}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br /><ref name=\"UK\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Mama Cry\"\n|2018\n|\u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Mama Cry\" did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, but peaked at number 14 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ynw-melly/chart-history/HBU|title=YNW Melly Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n* RIAA: Gold<ref name=\"RIAA\"/>\n|''I Am You''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"[[Mixed Personalities]]\"<br />{{small|(featuring [[Kanye West]])}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2019\n| 42 || 19 || \u2014 || 51 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 97\n|\n* RIAA: Platinum<ref name=\"RIAA\" />\n|''We All Shine''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"6 Kiss\"<br />{{small|([[Trippie Redd]] featuring [[Juice Wrld]] and YNW Melly)}}\n| 60 || 28 || \u2014 || 64 || \u2014 || 15 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| ''[[A Love Letter to You 4]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Bang Bang\"\n| \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Bang Bang\" did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, but peaked at number 7 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ynw-melly/chart-history/HBU|title=YNW Melly Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>}} || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 28 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Melly vs. Melvin''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|\"Two Face\"\n|\u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"Two Face\" did not enter the ''Billboard'' Hot 100, but peaked at number 22 on the [[Bubbling Under Hot 100]] chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/ynw-melly/chart-history/HBU|title=YNW Melly Chart History: Bubbling Under Hot 100|work=Billboard|accessdate=March 26, 2020}}</ref>}}\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{YNW Melly}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Melly, YNW}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:People from Indian River County, Florida]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Florida]]\n[[Category:American prisoners and detainees]]\n[[Category:Bloods]]\n[[Category:African-American male rappers]]\n[[Category:Southern hip hop musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{short description |American rapper, singer, and songwriter from Florida}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name               = YNW Melly\n| image              = YNW Melly - Mug shot (2019).jpg\n| caption            = YNW Melly's mugshot in February 2019\n| birth_name         = Jamell Maurice Demons<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heavy.com/news/2018/06/ynw-melly-arrested/|title=YNW Melly Arrested: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|author=Stephanie Dube Dwilson|date=June 30, 2018|website=[[Heavy.com]]|accessdate=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|year=1999|month=5|day=1}}\n| birth_place        = [[Gifford, Florida]], U.S.<ref name=bill>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8471446/ynw-melly-i-am-you-mixtape-tee-grizzley-lion-king-interview|title=YNW Melly on Breakout Mixtape 'I Am You,' Interpolating Chris Brown Throwbacks & His Favorite 'Lion King' Solos|date=August 21, 2018|author=Charles Holmes|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Rapper\n* singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| years_active       = 2017\u2013present\n| home_town          =\n| awards             = \n| background = solo_singer\n| instrument = Vocals\n| genre = {{flatlist| \n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[trap music|trap]]\n* [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| label = [[300 Entertainment|300]]\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Kanye West]]\n* [[Lil B]]\n* [[Lil Keed]]\n* [[Tee Grizzley]]\n}}\n| website = \n}}\n\n'''Jamell Maurice Demons''' (born May 1, 1999), known professionally as '''YNW Melly''', is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter from [[Gifford, Florida]].<ref name=\"fader2018\">{{cite web |last1=Dandridge-Lemco |first1=Ben |title=YNW Melly premieres new video for 'Murder on My Mind' |url=http://www.thefader.com/2018/08/03/ynw-melly-murder-on-my-mind-video-premiere |website=thefader |accessdate=August 5, 2018 |date=August 3, 2018}}</ref> He is best known for his songs \"[[Murder on My Mind]]\" and \"[[Mixed Personalities]]\" featuring [[Kanye West]]. His single \"Murder on My Mind\" is considered YNW Melly's breakout, which garnered even further attention after the rapper was charged with double-murder. He released his debut album, ''We All Shine'', on January 17, 2019, to generally positive reviews from music critics.\n\nIn February 2019, he was arrested and charged with two counts of first-degree murder and faces life in prison or the [[death penalty]] if convicted.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/ynw-melly-arrested-double-murder-794588/|title=YNW Melly Charged With Two Counts of First-Degree Murder|first1=Charles|last1=Holmes|first2=Charles|last2=Holmes|date=February 14, 2019|publisher=|accessdate=February 14, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/music/news/ynw-melly-double-murder-kanye-west-1203139808/|title=YNW Melly, Kanye West Collaborator, Arrested for Double Murder|first=Jem|last=Aswad|date=February 14, 2019|publisher=Variety|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/florida-prosecutors-to-seek-death-penalty-for-ynw-melly/amp/|title=Florida Prosecutors to Seek Death Penalty for YNW Melly|accessdate=April 22, 2019|publisher=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref> He is also a suspect in the 2017 murder of a sheriff's deputy in Gifford.<ref name=\"Complex\"/> In March 2019, Demons pleaded not guilty to the double-murder charges and is currently awaiting trial.<ref>https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8501228/ynw-melly-pleads-not-guilty-double-murder-charges</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nYNW Melly was born on May 1, 1999, in [[Gifford, Florida]] to father Jamie Demons and mother Donte Taylor.{{citation needed|date=January 2020}} Demons was raised by his single mother. She was 14 years old when she became pregnant with him, giving birth to him in the [[ninth grade]]. Later moving to a poorer part of [[Gifford, Florida|Gifford]], his mother struggled to pay for housing and necessaries. Demons joined the [[Bloods]] gang at a young age,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tcpalm.com/story/news/crime/2019/02/15/who-florida-rapper-ynw-melly-accused-murdering-childhood-friends/2881599002/|title=Gifford rapper YNW Melly documentary gives eerie look at friendship with murdered artists|last=Moore|first=Mary Helen|website=TCPalm|language=en|access-date=2019-11-22}}</ref> later posting his songs on [[SoundCloud]] when he was 15. In late 2015, Demons was arrested for shooting at a group of students near [[Vero Beach High School]] and subsequently convicted of aggravated battery, discharging a firearm in public, and two counts of aggravated assault, for which he served several months in prison.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2018/08/02/ynw-melly-virtual-i-am-you-gen-f-interview|title=How YNW Melly turned his pain into beautiful rap ballads|website=The FADER|language=en|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wlna-webservice.gannettdigital.com/articleservice/view/2868483002/michigan-state-spartans/24.3.57/iphone?apiKey=57646bc6bca4811fea00000126a000bb69414f2a44f75039173cf104|title=Grand jury indictment: YNW Melly fired the gun, killing the friends he grew up with|website=USA Today|language=en|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n=== 2017-2018: Early fame and debut projects ===\nIn late 2017, while still incarcerated, Demons released his first project, an [[extended play|EP]] called ''Collect Call'', which contained features from numerous well-known artists, including [[Lil B]] and John Wicks. In 2018, he released the singles \"Virtual (Blue Balenciagas)\", \"Melly the Menace\", and \"Slang That Iron\". Other singles include \"4 Real\", \"Butter Pecan\", and \"Medium Fries\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Fred |first1=Thomas |title=YNW Melly |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/ynw-melly-mn0003736777/biography |publisher=AllMusic |accessdate=August 5, 2018}}</ref> The respective music videos have amassed 26 million, 16 million and 11 million views on [[YouTube]], as of January 2019.\n\nIn August 2018, Demons released his debut mixtape ''I Am You,'' which later appeared on the [[Billboard 200]] at number 192 on January 10, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.49905/title.hip-hop-album-sales-a-boogie-wit-da-hoodie-scores-his-first-no-1-album-on-billboard-200|title=Hip Hop Album Sales: A Boogie Wit Da Hoodie Earns His 1st No. 1 Album On Billboard 200|date=2019-01-14|website=HipHopDX|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019-present: Second mixtape and debut studio album ===\nOn January 17, 2019, while incarcerated, Demons released ''We All Shine'', his second commercial mixtape, consisting of 16 tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/ynw-melly-drops-we-all-shine-featuring-kanye-west-new-mixtape.118819.html|title=YNW Melly Drops \"We All Shine\" Featuring Kanye West|website=HotNewHipHop|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref> The project featured collaborations with [[Kanye West]] and Fredo Bang.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.49950/title.ynw-melly-releases-we-all-shine-project-with-kanye-west-guest-appearance|title=YNW Melly Releases \"We All Shine\" Project With Kanye West Guest Appearance|date=2019-01-17|website=HipHopDX|access-date=2019-01-18}}</ref> A music video for \"Mixed Personalities\" featuring West was released with the album.\n\nAs of March 2019, Demons had amassed over 200 million streams on [[Spotify]] with over 10 million monthly listeners. His most streamed song was \"[[Murder on My Mind]]\", which was originally released as a single before being added to ''I Am You''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.spotify.com/artist/1cNDP5yjU5vjeR8qMf4grg|title=YNW Melly|website=Spotify|accessdate=February 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 22, 2019, Demons released his debut studio album, ''[[Melly vs. Melvin]]''. It peaked at number eight on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], making it his highest charting album at the time. The album included the singles \"[[223's]]\", which peaked at number 34 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]].\n\nOn March 13, 2020, Demons released a remix of his track \"Suicidal\", making it the second single from ''Melly vs. Melvin''. The remix included a feature from late rapper [[Juice Wrld]], making it his third official posthumous feature. The song has peaked at number 20 on the Hot 100. \n\n==Legal issues==\nDemons was arrested on June 30, 2018, in Fort Myers, Florida for possession of marijuana, possession of weapon or ammunition by a convicted felon and drug paraphernalia.<ref>{{cite book|title=Jamell Maurice Demons Arrest Information|date=June 30, 2018|publisher=Lee County Sheriff's Office |location=Ft Myers, FL|url=http://www.sheriffleefl.org/how_do_i/learn_more_about/arrest_search/index.php?view=inmateDetail&id=881998 |accessdate=June 30, 2018}}</ref>\n\nDemons was again arrested on January 3, 2019, in Fort Myers for possession of marijuana.<ref>{{cite book|title=Jamell Maurice Demons Arrest Information|date=Jan 3, 2019|publisher=Lee County Sheriff's Office |location=Ft Myers, FL|url=http://www.sheriffleefl.org/how_do_i/learn_more_about/arrest_search/index.php?view=inmateDetail&id=894574 |accessdate=January 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 12, 2019, Demons was charged with two counts of first-degree murder in connection with the October 2018 shooting deaths in [[Fort Lauderdale, Florida|Fort Lauderdale]] of two men described as his close friends, aspiring rappers Anthony \"YNW Sakchaser\" Williams, 21, and Christopher \"YNW Juvy\" Thomas Jr., 19. Authorities purport that Demons conspired with fellow YNW rapper Cortlen Henry, also known as YNW Bortlen, to stage the double-murder of Williams and Thomas Jr. and make it appear as if they were fatally injured in a drive by shooting. Henry allegedly drove the victims to the hospital where they later succumbed to their wounds.<ref>{{cite book|title=Jamell Maurice Demons Arrest Information|date=February 13, 2019|publisher=Miramar Police, FL |location=Miramar, FL|url=http://apps.sheriff.org/ArrestSearch/InmateDetail/371900050|accessdate=February 13, 2019}}</ref> Demons turned himself in on February 13, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Johnson |first1=Jazzi |title=Florida Rapper YNW Melly Turns Himself In After Being Charged In The Killings Of His Best Friends - Blavity |url=https://blavity.com/florida-rapper-ynw-melly-turns-himself-in-after-being-charged-in-the-killings-of-his-best-friends |website=blavity.com |accessdate=5 August 2019}}</ref> He announced on his Instagram that\n{{Quote\n|text= \u2033No I did not get locked up in Washington , but I am turning myself in today... a couple months ago I lost my two brothers by violence and now the system want to find justice.. unfortunately a lot of rumors and lies are being said but no worries god is with me and my brother @ynw.bortlen and we want y\u2019all to remember it\u2019s a ynw Family I love you\u2033\n|author= @ynwmelly\n}}\n\nOn February 22, 2019, ''[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]'' reported that Demons and Cortlen Henry (YNW Bortlen) are now suspects in the fatal 2017 shooting of off-duty [[Indian River County, Florida|Indian River County]] Sheriff's Department deputy Gary Chambliss in Gifford.<ref name=\"Complex\">{{cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2019/02/ynw-melly-suspect-deputy-shooting-death|title=YNW Melly Reportedly Now a Suspect in Deputy's Shooting Death|first=Trace William|last=Cowen|date=February 22, 2019|publisher=Complex|accessdate=February 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Coronavirus diagnosis ==\nOn April 2, 2020, YNW Melly (via management)  told fans on Twitter that he tested positive for [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/ynw-melly-tests-positive-for-covid-19-in-jail/|title=YNW Melly Tests Positive for COVID-19 in Jail|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>As of April 2-3, 2020, he is in the process of trying to get an early release from prison due to health concerns. This happened hours after [[6ix9ine]] got released from prison due to [[asthma]] and [[bronchitis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/tekashi-6ix9ine-home-confinement-request-approved-coronavirus-outbreak-2020-4|title=Tekashi 6ix9ine has been released from prison to serve the rest of his sentence at home because of the coronavirus|last=McLaughlin|first=Kelly|website=Insider|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio album===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:22em;\"| Album details\n! colspan=\"3\" | Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8545115/trippie-redd-no-1-album-billboard-200-chart|title=Trippie Redd Rules With First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=December 1, 2019|accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US<br>R&B/<br>HH]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2019/12/01/lennies-dance-butts-celine-2nd-place|title=Lennie's 'Dance' Butts Celine Into 2nd Place|website=FYIMusicNews|date=December 1, 2019|accessdate=December 3, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Melly vs. Melvin]]''\n|\n* Released: November 22, 2019\n* Label: [[300 Entertainment|300]]\n* Formats: [[Music download|Digital download]], [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| 8 || 3 || 17\n|}\n\n===Mixtapes===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:22em;\"| Album details\n! co