{"title_page": "Andrzej Duda", "text_new": "{{short description|Polish politician, President of Poland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name  = Andrzej Duda\n| image = Andrzej_Duda_portret.JPG\n| imagesize = \n| office = [[President of Poland]]\n| term_start = 6 August 2015\n| term_end = \n| primeminister = [[Ewa Kopacz]]<br />[[Beata Szyd\u0142o]]<br />[[Mateusz Morawiecki]]\n| predecessor = [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]\n| successor = \n| office1 = [[Member of the European Parliament]]\n| constituency1 = [[Lesser Poland and \u015awi\u0119tokrzyskie (European Parliament constituency)|10 - Krak\u00f3w]]\n| term_start1 = 1 July 2014\n| term_end1 = 6 August 2015\n| office2 = [[Sejm|Member of the Sejm]]\n| term_start2 = 8 November 2011\n| term_end2 = 1 July 2014\n| constituency2 = [[Krak\u00f3w II (parliamentary constituency)|13 - Krak\u00f3w II]]\n| office3 = [[Local government in Krak\u00f3w|Member of the Krak\u00f3w City Council]] \n| term_start3 = 2 December 2010\n| term_end3 = 8 November 2011\n| constituency3 = 2 - [[Pr\u0105dnik Bia\u0142y]]/[[Krowodrza]]\n| office4= [[Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland|Undersecretary of State in the Chancellery of the President]]\n| term_start4 = 16 January 2008\n| term_end4 = 6 July 2010\n| president4  = [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]]<br>''vacant''<br>\n| office5= [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Undersecretary of State in the Ministry of Justice]]\n| term_start5 = 1 August 2006\n| term_end5 = 15 November 2007\n| minister5  = [[Zbigniew Ziobro]]\n| birth_name = Andrzej Sebastian Duda\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|05|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Krak\u00f3w]], [[Polish People's Republic|Poland]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Independent politician|Independent]] {{small|(2015\u2013present)}}\n| otherparty =[[Law and Justice]] {{small|(2005\u20132015)}}<br />[[Freedom Union (Poland)|Freedom Union]] {{small|(2000\u20132001)}}\n| spouse = [[Agata Kornhauser-Duda|Agata Kornhauser]] {{small|(m. 1994)}}\n| children = Kinga\n| residence = [[Presidential Palace, Warsaw|Presidential Palace]]\n| alma_mater = [[Jagiellonian University]]\n| signature = Andrzej Duda Signature 02.svg\n| salary = ~[[EUR|\u20ac]]68,000, annual <ref>{{cite web|url=https://zarobki.pracuj.pl/Error|title=Strona nie istnieje - zarobki.pracuj.pl|author=|date=|website=zarobki.pracuj.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xe.com/currencyconverter/convert/?Amount=294000&From=PLN&To=EUR|title=294000 PLN to EUR - Convert Polish Zlotych to Euros - XE|author=|date=|website=www.xe.com|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n| awards = [[File:POL Order Or\u0142a Bia\u0142ego BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of the White Eagle (Poland)]] [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Wielki BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of Polonia Restituta]] [[File:POR Ordem do Merito Gra-Cruz BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of Merit (Portugal)]] [[File:Grand_Crest_Ordre_de_Leopold.png|40px|link=Order of Leopold (Belgium)]] [[File:CZE_Rad_Bileho_Lva_1_tridy_BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of White Lion (Czech Republic)]] [[File:Order Stara planina ribbon.png|40px|link=Order of Stara Planina (Bulgaria)]] [[File:St Olavs Orden storkors stripe.svg|40px|link=Order of St. Olav]] [[File:Star of Romania Ribbon.PNG|40px|link=Order of the Star of Romania]] [[File:FIN Order of the White Rose Grand Cross BAR.png|40px|link=Order of the White Rose of Finland]] [[File:GRE Order Redeemer 1Class.png|40px|link=Order of the Redeemer]] [[File:LVA Order of the Three Stars - Commander BAR.png|40px|link=Order of the Three Stars]] [[File:LTU Order of Vytautas the Great with the Golden Chain BAR.png|40px]] [[File:SVK Rad Bieleho Dvojkriza 1 triedy BAR.svg|40px]]\n| honorific_suffix = \n}}\n'''Andrzej Sebastian Duda''' ({{small|Polish pronunciation:}} {{IPAc-pl|AUD|Pl-Andrzej_Duda.ogg|\u02c8|a|n|d|\u0290|\u025b|j|-|\u02c8|d|u|d|a}}; born 16 May 1972) is a [[Poles|Polish]] lawyer and politician who serves as the current [[List of heads of state of Poland#Republic of Poland (1989\u2013present)|President of Poland]], holding the office since 6 August 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/05/24/andrzej-duda-elected-president-poland_n_7432554.html|title=Andrzej Duda Elected Poland's New President, Incumbent Bronislaw Komorowski Concedes Defeat|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=25 May 2015}}</ref> Before his tenure as President, Duda was a member of Polish Lower House ([[Sejm]]) from 2011 to 2014 and the [[European Parliament]] from 2014 to 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mularczyk|first1=Arkadiusz|title=Lista kandydat\u00f3w na zast\u0119pc\u00f3w przewodnicz\u0105cego i cz\u0142onk\u00f3w Trybuna\u0142u Stanu|url=http://orka.sejm.gov.pl/Druki6ka.nsf/0/1A8000B1E3780FA8C125738C00554FC5/$file/3.pdf|website=Sejm of the Republic of Poland|publisher=|accessdate=31 January 2015|language=pl}}</ref>\n\nDuda was the presidential candidate for the [[right wing]] [[Law and Justice]] party, during the [[2015 Polish presidential election|2015 presidential election]] in May 2015. In the first round of voting, Duda received 5,179,092 votes \u2013 34.76% of valid votes. In the second round of voting, Duda received 51.55% of the vote, beating the incumbent president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]], who received 48.45% of the vote. On 26 May 2015, Duda resigned his party membership as the president-elect. On October 24, 2019 he received the official support from PiS ahead of his re-election campaign in [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]].\n\n== Early life ==\nDuda was born in [[Krak\u00f3w]], to Janina Milewska and Jan Tadeusz Duda, professors at the [[AGH University of Science and Technology]]. His grandfather fought in the [[Polish\u2013Soviet War]] and later was a member of the [[Home Army (Poland)|Home Army]] during the [[Second World War]].<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\">{{cite news|title=Duda story \u2013 historia mi\u0142o\u015bci, podboju g\u00f3r i niespodziewanego wej\u015bcia w polityk\u0119|url=http://niezalezna.pl/64196-duda-story-historia-milosci-podboju-gor-i-niespodziewanego-wejscia-w-polityke|accessdate=30 May 2015|date=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuda attended [[Jan III Sobieski High School, Krak\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rodzina Dud\u00f3w: nowy prezydent jest zapalonym narciarzem i molem ksi\u0105\u017ckowym. Jego \u017cona to wymagaj\u0105ca nauczycielka|url=http://www.tvp.info/20194423/rodzina-dudow-nowy-prezydent-jest-zapalonym-narciarzem-i-molem-ksiazkowym-jego-zona-to-wymagajaca-nauczycielka|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=TVP}}</ref> He subsequently studied law at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. In October 2001 he was appointed as an assistant (holding M.A.) in the Administrative Law Department of Jagiellonian University. In January 2005, Duda also obtained a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] degree in law at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. Due to his political career, he has been mostly on unpaid leave (from the university) since September 2006, except for a 13-month interval beginning in September 2010, when he returned to the university.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andrzej Duda od blisko 9 lat jest na urlopie bezp\u0142atnym z UJ|url=http://www.rmf24.pl/raport-wybory-prezydenckie2015/najnowsze-fakty/news-andrzej-duda-od-blisko-9-lat-jest-na-urlopie-bezplatnym-z-uj,nId,1735152|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=RMF FM|date=18 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Political career ==\n[[File:Andrzej Duda Lech Kaczynski.jpg|thumb|left|Former President [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]] appointing Duda as undersecretary of state in the Chancellery of the President, 16 January 2008]]\nDuda began his political career with the now-defunct [[Freedom Union (Poland)|Freedom Union]] Party in the early 2000s. After the parliamentary elections in 2005, he began his collaboration with the [[Law and Justice]] Party (PiS).<ref name=\"Micha\u0142 Krzymowski Anna Szulc2015\">{{cite web |url=http://polska.newsweek.pl/andrzej-duda-byl-dzialaczem-unii-wolnosci,artykuly,359002,1.html#fp=nw |author=Micha\u0142 Krzymowski, Anna Szulc |title=Andrzej Duda by\u0142 dzia\u0142aczem Unii Wolno\u015bci |website=newsweek.pl |date=14 March 2015 |access-date=14 March 2015 |language=Polish |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150423090718/http://polska.newsweek.pl/andrzej-duda-byl-dzialaczem-unii-wolnosci,artykuly,359002,1.html#fp=nw |archive-date=23 April 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> From 2006 to 2007, Andrzej Duda was an undersecretary of state in the [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Ministry of Justice]]. Then, from 2007 to 2008, Duda was a member of the [[Polish State Tribunal]].\n\nFrom 2008 to 2010, during the presidency of [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]], Duda was an undersecretary of state in the [[Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.andrzejduda.pl/o-mnie |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526110639/http://m.andrzejduda.pl/o-mnie |url-status=dead |archive-date=26 May 2015 |title=Andrzej Duda |work=andrzejduda.pl }}</ref> In 2010, he was an unsuccessful candidate to become the Mayor of Krak\u00f3w as a PiS candidate,<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2010\">{{cite web |url = http://wybory2010.pkw.gov.pl/geo/pl/120000/126101.html#tabs-4 |title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2010 |access-date=24 November 2010|language=Polish}}</ref> but was more successful in the 2011 parliamentary election, where he received 79,981 votes for the Krak\u00f3w area, and thus became member of the [[Sejm]].<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2011\">{{cite web |url = http://wybory2011.pkw.gov.pl/wsw/pl/sjm-13.html |title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2011 |access-date=28 October 2011|language=Polish}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, the [[news magazine]] ''[[Polityka]]'' commended Duda for being one of the most active members of parliament, at the time, describing him as being open to opposition arguments and as refraining from personal attacks, as part of his role at the Commission for Constitutional Responsibility.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Paradowska|first1=Janina|last2=D\u0105browska|first2=Anna|title=Pos\u0142owie na medal i pos\u0142owie z nagan\u0105|url=http://www.polityka.pl/tygodnikpolityka/kraj/1556381,1,ranking-poslow-polityki-rozstrzygniety.read|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=Polityka|date=26 September 2013}}</ref> Duda remained a member of the Sejm until he was elected to the [[European Parliament]] in 2014.<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2014\">{{cite web|url=http://pe2014.pkw.gov.pl/pl/|title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2014|access-date=27 May 2014|language=Polish|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140824100453/http://pe2014.pkw.gov.pl/pl/|archive-date=24 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 Presidential Campaign ===\n{{main|2015 Polish presidential election}}\nIn the shade of the upcoming expiration of president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]'s first term, Komorowski was able to seek re-election in a scheduled presidential election. Duda was Komorowski's [[Law and Justice]] rival in the election.\n\nIn the first round of the [[2015 Polish presidential election|2015 presidential election]], Duda came first, receiving 5,179,092 votes and thus 34.76% of valid votes.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://prezydent2015.pkw.gov.pl/pliki/1_Obwieszczenie.pdf |title=Obwieszczenie Pa\u0144stwowej Komisji Wyborczej z dnia 11 maja 2015 r. o wynikach g\u0142osowania i wyniku wybor\u00f3w Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej, zarz\u0105dzonych na dzie\u0144 10 maja 2015 r. |access-date=12 May 2015 |website=pkw.gov.pl|language=Polish}}</ref>\n\nIn the second round Duda took 51.55% of the vote against the 48.45% share of his rival, then-incumbent president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prezydent2015.pkw.gov.pl/325_Ponowne_glosowanie|title=PKW \u2013 www.prezydent.2015.pkw.gov.pl|work=pkw.gov.pl}}</ref> On 26 May 2015, he officially resigned from party membership.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andrzej Duda ju\u017c poza PiS. Zrzek\u0142 si\u0119 cz\u0142onkostwa|url=http://www.tvp.info/20215021/andrzej-duda-juz-poza-pis-zrzekl-sie-czlonkostwa|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Presidency ==\n[[File:Andrzej Duda Bogdan Borusewicz Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska Zgromadzenie Narodowe 6 sierpnia 2015 01.JPG|thumb|Andrzej Duda taking the oath of office, 6 August 2015]]\n[[File:Wsp\u00f3lne o\u015bwiadczenie w sprawie ustanowienia wszechstronnego strategicznego partnerstwa.jpg|thumb|Duda and [[Xi Jinping]] signed a declaration on strategic partnership]]\n[[File:President Trump's Trip to Poland (34920988424) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Duda and his wife Agata Kornhauser-Duda with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and [[Melania Trump]] in Warsaw]]\nThe five-year term of Andrzej Duda began on 6 August 2015 with taking an oath of office during a [[National Assembly (Poland)|National Assembly]] session.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,5,uroczystosci-inauguracji-prezydenta-rp-andrzeja-dudy.html|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150806134223/http://prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,5,uroczystosci-inauguracji-prezydenta-rp-andrzeja-dudy.html|url-status=dead|title=Oficjalna strona Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej / Aktualno\u015bci /\u2026|date=6 August 2015|archivedate=6 August 2015|website=archive.is|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nDuda rejected the [[European Union]]'s proposal of [[European migrant crisis#Relocation and resettlement of asylum seekers|migrant quotas to redistribute asylum seekers]], saying: \"I won\u2019t agree to a dictate of the strong. I won\u2019t back a Europe where the economic advantage of the size of a population will be a reason to force solutions on other countries regardless of their national interests\".<ref>\"[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-09-08/polish-president-blasts-eu-dictate-of-the-strong-on-migrants Poland's Duda Blasts EU `Dictate of the Strong' on Migrants]\". ''Bloomberg.'' 8 September 2015.</ref>\n\nEventually former Prime Minister [[Ewa Kopacz]] declared that Poland, as an expression of \u201cEuropean solidarity\u201d, would take in 2,000 people over the next two years, mainly from Syria and Eritrea (out of 3,700 originally requested).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/10/opinion/poland-shouldnt-shut-out-refugees.html|title=Opinion - Poland Shouldn\u2019t Shut Out Refugees|first=Konstanty|last=Gebert|date=9 September 2015|publisher=|access-date=6 February 2018|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nDuda and Croatian President [[Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovi\u0107]] were the originators of the [[Three Seas Initiative]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvn24.pl/magazyn-tvn24/wielki-plan-malych-panstw-jak-trojmorze-wzmocni-lub-podzieli-unie,106,1968|title=Wielki plan ma\u0142ych pa\u0144stw. Jak Tr\u00f3jmorze wzmocni lub podzieli Uni\u0119|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuda repeatedly met with [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] of the [[Communist Party of China]] and China's leader, [[Xi Jinping]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Xi Jinping Holds Talks with President Andrzej Duda of Poland, Two Heads of State Decide to Promote Development Level of China-Poland Strategic Partnership |url=http://www.chinaembassy.se/eng/wjdt/t1319025.htm |work=Chinaembassy.se |date=25 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=President Duda sends sympathy message to President Xi Jinping |url=https://www.thefirstnews.com/article/president-duda-sends-sympathy-message-to-president-xi-jinping-10277 |work=Polish Press Agency |date=3 February 2020}}</ref> stating that \"Polish companies will benefit hugely\" from China's [[Belt and Road Initiative]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Polish president says Xi Jinping understands central European dynamic |url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2016xivisitee/2016-06/19/content_25763414.htm |work=Chinadaily.com.cn |date=19 June 2016}}</ref> Duda and Xi signed a declaration on [[strategic partnership]] in which they reiterated that Poland and China viewed each other as long-term strategic partners.<ref>{{cite news |title=Xi welcomes Chinese freight train to 'strategic partner' Poland |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-poland-china-xi/xi-welcomes-chinese-freight-train-to-strategic-partner-poland-idUKKCN0Z6205 |agency=Reuters |date=20 June 2016}}</ref> Duda said that he hope Poland will become a gateway to Europe for China.<ref>{{cite news |title=Poland and China sign universal strategic partnership pact |url=http://archiwum.thenews.pl/1/10/Artykul/257974,Poland-and-China-sign-universal-strategic-partnership-pact |work=Radio Poland |date=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, his approval rating stood at 71% and in February 2018, at 72%, a record surpassed only by [[Aleksander Kwa\u015bniewski]], whose approval ratings surpassed 75% from 1995 to 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dorzeczy.pl/kraj/40293/Sondaz-CBOS-Wielki-wzrost-poparcia-dla-prezydenta-Dudy.html|title=Sonda\u017c CBOS: Wielki wzrost poparcia dla prezydenta Dudy|trans-title=|language=|website=dorzeczy.pl|access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polityka/cbos-prezydent-duda-z-najwiekszym-poparciem-premier-morawiecki-na-drugim-miejscu/lr073kx|title=Prezydent Duda z najwi\u0119kszym poparciem|trans-title=|language=|website=fakt.pl|access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism and controversies ===\nIn November 2015, basing on Art. 139 of the [[Constitution of Poland]], Duda pardoned former [[Central Anticorruption Bureau]] (CBA) head [[Mariusz Kami\u0144ski]] and three CBA officers convicted by a court of 1st instance in the so-called \"[[:pl:Afera gruntowa|Land Affair]]\",<ref>\"[http://www.pap.pl/aktualnosci/news,432779,prezydent-ulaskawil-min-b-szefa-cba-mariusza-kaminskiego.html]\". ''Polska Agencja Prasowa'', 17 November 2015.</ref> marking the first pardon granted by a president before reaching a final verdict.<ref>Marek Domagalski. Prezydencka \u0142aska dzieli prawnik\u00f3w. ''Rzeczpospolita'', p. C2, 19 November 2015.</ref> According to some lawyers (including professors Jan Zimmermann \u2013 Andrzej Duda's doctorate promoter, Leszek Kubicki \u2013 former [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Minister of Justice]] and [[Andrzej Zoll]] \u2013 former president of the [[Constitutional Tribunal (Poland)|Constitutional Tribunal]]) Duda breached the Constitution of Poland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/opinie/artykuly/507262,prof-jan-zimmermann-z-uj-prezydent-andrzej-duda-zlamal-konstytucje-trzykrotnie.html|title=\"Prezydent z\u0142ama\u0142 konstytucj\u0119 przynajmniej trzykrotnie\". Promotor Andrzeja Dudy krytykuje swojego doktoranta|author=|date=|website=wiadomosci.dziennik.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref><ref>[http://wyborcza.pl/1,75478,19210341,czy-prezydent-zlamal-konstytucje-prawnicy-podzieleni.html Ewa Siedlecka, ''Wyborcza.pl'', 18 November 2015]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://polskatimes.pl/prof-andrzej-zoll-prezydent-duda-zlamal-prawo/ar/9099824|title=Prof. Andrzej Zoll: Prezydent Duda z\u0142ama\u0142 prawo|first=Maria|last=Mazurek|date=19 November 2015|website=polskatimes.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAndrzej Duda has refused to [[Oath of office|swear in]] any of the five [[Constitutional Tribunal (Poland)|Constitutional Tribunal]] judge candidates selected by the [[Sejm]] of the VII term. Three of those were selected since 7 November 2015 whose election was declared constitutional.<ref>\"[http://isap.sejm.gov.pl/DetailsServlet?id=WDU20150002129]\". ''Dziennik Ustaw'' from 2015, pos. 2129</ref> On 3 and 9 December 2015 Duda swore in five other candidates for the same office selected by the Sejm of the VIII term.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20151203124052/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art%2C75%2Cprezydent-odebral-slubowanie-od-sedziow-tk.html]\". prezydent.pl, 3 December 2015</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,80,prezydent-przyjal-slubowanie-od-sedzi-tk-julii-przylebskiej.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226082006/https://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,80,prezydent-przyjal-slubowanie-od-sedzi-tk-julii-przylebskiej.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=26 December 2015|title=prezydent.pl, 9 December 2015|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 December 2015, Duda signed the Constitutional Tribunal bill (passed on 22 December 2015 by the Sejm), which unequivocally breaches the Constitution of Poland according to the National Council of the Judiciary of Poland,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krs.pl/pl/aktualnosci/d,2015,12/3872,stanowisko-prezydium-krajowej-rady-sadownictwa-w-sprawie-uchwalonej-22-grudnia-2015-r-zmiany-ustawy-o-trybunale-konstytucyjnym-dz-u-poz-1064-ze-zm|title=Aktualno\u015bci - Stanowisko Prezydium Krajowej Rady S\u0105downictwa w sprawie uchwalonej 22 grudnia 2015 r. zmiany ustawy o Trybunale Konstytucyjnym (Dz. U. poz. 1064 ze zm.) - Krajowa Rada S\u0105downictwa|author=|date=|website=www.krs.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref> the [[Public Prosecutor General (Poland)|Public Prosecutor General]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/polityka/artykuly/508968,prokurator-generalny-o-nowelizacji-ustawy-o-trybunale-konstytucyjnym.html|title=Nowelizacja ustawy o TK. Prokurator Generalny straszy parali\u017cem prac|author=|date=|website=wiadomosci.dziennik.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref> and the [[Polish Ombudsman]].<ref>[http://www.rp.pl/Sedziowie-i-sady/312249956-RPO-i-HFPC-apeluja--do-prezydenta-ws-noweli-ustawy-o-TK.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180102013150/http://www.rp.pl/Sedziowie-i-sady/312249956-RPO-i-HFPC-apeluja--do-prezydenta-ws-noweli-ustawy-o-TK.html |date=2 January 2018 }}, rp.pl, 24 December 2015</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Duda rejected appointing 10 judges selected by the National Council of the Judiciary of Poland.<ref>Ewa Siedlecka, \"Prezydent s\u0105dzi s\u0119dzi\u00f3w\", ''[[Gazeta Wyborcza]]'', p. 1, 29 June 2016</ref><!-- this does not explain how it is either a criticism or controversy -->\n\nIn July 2017, Duda informed the public he had decided to veto two controversial judicial bills backed by the government and passed by both houses of the Polish parliament. The President's spokesman subsequently said that the third act \u2013 the common courts bill \u2013 would be signed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.president.pl/en/news/art,508,president-to-veto-two-judicial-bills-says-will-sign-bill-on-common-courts.html|title=President of the Republic of Poland / News / President to veto two judicial bills, says will sign bill on common courts|website=www.president.pl|accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref> The veto was just one example of Duda opposing the policies of PiS.<ref name=\"veconomist\" >{{cite news|author=|title=Poland\u2019s president turns on his former boss|url=https://www.economist.com/news/europe/21730165-ruling-law-and-justice-partys-plan-nobble-polish-institutions-hits-roadblock-polands|work=[[The Economist]]|date=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, Duda said that he would sign into law [[Amendment to the Act on the Institute of National Remembrance|the \"Holocaust bill\"]], making it illegal to accuse 'the Polish nation' of complicity in the Holocaust and other Nazi atrocities, a measure that has roiled relations with Israel and the United States, with Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] going as far as accusing the Polish government of [[Holocaust denial]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/01/27/it-could-soon-be-a-crime-to-blame-poland-for-nazi-atrocities-and-israel-is-appalled/|title=Analysis {{!}} It could soon be a crime to blame Poland for Nazi atrocities, and Israel is appalled|last=Selk|first=Avi|date=27 January 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=28 January 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/06/world/europe/poland-holocaust-law.html|title=Poland\u2019s President Supports Making Some Holocaust Statements a Crime|first=Marc|last=Santora|date=6 February 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-israel-poland/polands-president-duda-says-will-sign-holocaust-bill-into-law-idUSKBN1FQ1EQ|title=Polish president signs Holocaust bill, triggers Israeli, U.S. criticism|first=Pawel|last=Sobczak|date=6 February 2018|work=Reuters|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDuda is married to [[Agata Kornhauser-Duda]], a teacher of [[German language|German]] language at Jan III Sobieski High School in Krak\u00f3w.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teachers|url=http://www.sobieski.krakow.pl/o-szkole/nauczyciele/}}</ref> They had met at a party while still attending rival schools<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\"/> and have been married since 21 December 1994.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wantuch|first1=Dominika|title=Agata Kornhauser-Duda. Pierwsza Dama w stylu zachodnim|url=http://krakow.gazeta.pl/krakow/1,44425,17983045,Agata_Kornhauser_Duda__Pierwsza_Dama_w_stylu_zachodnim.html|accessdate=28 May 2015|agency=Gazeta Wyborcza|date=25 May 2015}}</ref> Together they have one daughter, Kinga, born in 1995, who also graduated in law in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Andrzej Duda opublikowa\u0142 zdj\u0119cie c\u00f3rki na Instagramie. Pochwali\u0142 si\u0119 jej sukcesem |url=https://natemat.pl/272777,kinga-duda-skonczyla-studia-andrzej-duda-pochwalil-sie-na-instagramie |website=naTemat.pl |accessdate=25 May 2019 |language=pl}}</ref> His father-in-law is [[Julian Kornhauser]], a well-known writer, translator and literary critic.<ref>Marek Bartosik, [http://www.gazetakrakowska.pl/artykul/334041,andrzej-duda-spozniony-pociag-do-polityki,id,t.html Andrzej Duda: sp\u00f3\u017aniony poci\u0105g do polityki] Gazeta Krakowska 19 November 2010 {{in lang|pl}}</ref>\n\nHe is a keen skier and while studying participated in the Polish Academic Championships in the [[Alpine skiing]] category.<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\"/>\n\nDuda is a Catholic. He took part in religious ceremonies on many occasions, including [[Midnight Mass]], the [[\u015awi\u0119conka|blessing of food]] on [[Holy Saturday]], or the [[Corpus Christi procession]] in [[Krak\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.se.pl/wiadomosci/polityka/prezydent-andrzej-duda-z-rodzina-na-pasterce-zdjecia_755537.html |title=Prezydent Andrzej Duda z rodzin\u0105 na pasterce [ZDJ\u0118CIA] |publisher=Super Express |work=katk |date=27 December 2015 |accessdate=21 April 2016 |language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fakt.pl/politycy/andrzej-duda-i-kinga-duda-w-kosciele-ze-swieconka,galeria,621054.html |title=Andrzej Duda z c\u00f3rk\u0105 \u015bwi\u0119ci jajeczko |publisher=Fakt |work=js |date=26 March 2016 |accessdate=21 April 2016 |language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://natemat.pl/151749,prezydent-i-koscioly-od-wyborow-andrzej-duda-ma-wiecej-zdjec-ze-mszy-niz-z-panstwowych-uroczystosci |title=Prezydent i ko\u015bcio\u0142y. Od wybor\u00f3w Andrzej Duda ma wi\u0119cej zdj\u0119\u0107 ze mszy ni\u017c z pa\u0144stwowych uroczysto\u015bci |publisher=natemat.pl |last=Sikora |first=Kamil |date=17 August 2015 |accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n=== National Honours===\n* {{flag|Poland}}: [[Order of the White Eagle (Poland)|Order of the White Eagle]] (''[[ex officio]]'')\n* {{flag|Poland}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of Polonia Restituta]] (''ex officio'')\n\n===Foreign Honours===\n* {{flag|Belgium}}: Gran Cordon of the [[Order of Leopold (Belgium)|Order of Leopold]] (2015)\n* {{flag|Bulgaria}}: I Class [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Bulgaria#Orders 4|Order of Stara Planina]] (\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430) (14 April 2016)<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.lex.bg/bg/laws/ldoc/2136801460 |title=\u0423\u043a\u0430\u0437 \u2116 99 \u043e\u0442 14.04.2016 \u0433. \u0417\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0433-\u043d \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0439 \u0414\u0443\u0434\u0430 \u2013 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u0448\u0430, \u0441 \u043e\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \"\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430\" \u0441 \u043b\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 |access-date=3 May 2016 |website=lex.bg |language=bg}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Czech Republic}}: Collar of the [[Order of the White Lion]] (15 March 2016)\n* {{flag|Finland}}: Grand Cross with Collar [[Order of the White Rose of Finland]] (2017)\n* {{flag|Greece}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Redeemer]] (2017)\n* {{flag|Latvia}}: Commander Grand Cross with Chain of the [[Order of the Three Stars]] (2018)\n* {{flag|Lithuania}}: Grand Cross with Golden Chain of the [[Order of Vytautas the Great]] (21 February 2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lrp.lt/en/|title=President of the Republic of Lithuania|author=|date=|website=www.lrp.lt|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Norway}}: Grand Cross of the Royal Norwegian [[Order of St. Olav]] (23 May 2016)\n* {{flag|Portugal}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of Merit (Portugal)|Order of Merit Grand Cross]] (2008)<ref>{{cite web |url = http://dre.pt/pdf2sdip/2009/02/040000000/0769107691.pdf |title=Chancelaria das Ordens Honor\u00edficas Portuguesas |access-date=12 September 2010 |website=dre.pt |language=pt}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Romania}}: Collar of the [[Order of the Star of Romania]] (10 July 2016)\n* {{flag|Slovakia}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of the White Double Cross]] (2019)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons}}\n{{Portal|Poland|Biography}}\n* [http://www.president.pl/en/president/biography Official Biography of President Andrzej Duda]\n* [http://www.president.pl/en/ The official website of the President of the Republic of Poland]\n* [http://www.sejm.gov.pl/english.html Polish Sejm]\n* [http://ludzie.wprost.pl/sylwetka/4102128/Andrzej-Duda.html Wprost] {{in lang|pl}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of Poland]]|years=2015\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Law and Justice]] nominee for <br /> [[President of Poland]]|years=[[2015 Polish presidential election|2015]] and [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|poland}}\n{{s-new|first}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Polish order of precedence|Order of precedence of Poland]]<br />''{{small|as President}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after={{nowrap|[[El\u017cbieta Witek]]}}|as=[[Marshal of the Sejm]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Heads of state of Poland}}\n{{Heads of state of the European Union Member states}}\n{{Candidates in the Polish presidential election, 2015}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Duda, Andrzej}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Candidates in the 2015 Polish presidential election]]\n[[Category:Jagiellonian University alumni]]\n[[Category:Law and Justice politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Poland 2009\u20132014]]\n[[Category:MEPs for Poland 2014\u20132019]]\n[[Category:People from Krak\u00f3w]]\n[[Category:Polish lawyers]]\n[[Category:Polish Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Presidents of Poland]]\n[[Category:Members of the Polish Sejm 2011\u20132015]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish politician, President of Poland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Andrzej Duda\n| image = Kancelaria Prezydenta RP Andrzeja Dudy 39.jpg\n| imagesize = \n| office = [[President of Poland]]\n| term_start = 6 August 2015\n| term_end = \n| primeminister = [[Ewa Kopacz]]<br />[[Beata Szyd\u0142o]]<br />[[Mateusz Morawiecki]]\n| predecessor = [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]\n| successor = \n| office1 = [[Member of the European Parliament]]\n| constituency1 = [[Lesser Poland and \u015awi\u0119tokrzyskie (European Parliament constituency)|10 - Krak\u00f3w]]\n| term_start1 = 1 July 2014\n| term_end1 = 6 August 2015\n| office2 = [[Sejm|Member of the Sejm]]\n| term_start2 = 8 November 2011\n| term_end2 = 1 July 2014\n| constituency2 = [[Krak\u00f3w II (parliamentary constituency)|13 - Krak\u00f3w II]]\n| office3 = [[Local government in Krak\u00f3w|Member of the Krak\u00f3w City Council]] \n| term_start3 = 2 December 2010\n| term_end3 = 8 November 2011\n| constituency3 = 2 - [[Pr\u0105dnik Bia\u0142y]]/[[Krowodrza]]\n| office4= [[Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland|Undersecretary of State in the Chancellery of the President]]\n| term_start4 = 16 January 2008\n| term_end4 = 6 July 2010\n| president4  = [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]]<br>''vacant''<br>\n| office5= [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Undersecretary of State in the Ministry of Justice]]\n| term_start5 = 1 August 2006\n| term_end5 = 15 November 2007\n| minister5  = [[Zbigniew Ziobro]]\n| birth_name = Andrzej Sebastian Duda\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|05|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Krak\u00f3w]], [[Polish People's Republic|Poland]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Independent politician|Independent]] {{small|(2015\u2013present)}}\n| otherparty =[[Law and Justice]] {{small|(2005\u20132015)}}<br />[[Freedom Union (Poland)|Freedom Union]] {{small|(2000\u20132001)}}\n| spouse = [[Agata Kornhauser-Duda|Agata Kornhauser]] {{small|(m. 1994)}}\n| children = Kinga\n| residence = [[Presidential Palace, Warsaw|Presidential Palace]]\n| alma_mater = [[Jagiellonian University]]\n| signature = Andrzej Duda Signature 02.svg\n| salary = ~[[EUR|\u20ac]]68,000, annual <ref>{{cite web|url=https://zarobki.pracuj.pl/Error|title=Strona nie istnieje - zarobki.pracuj.pl|author=|date=|website=zarobki.pracuj.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xe.com/currencyconverter/convert/?Amount=294000&From=PLN&To=EUR|title=294000 PLN to EUR - Convert Polish Zlotych to Euros - XE|author=|date=|website=www.xe.com|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n| awards = [[File:POL Order Or\u0142a Bia\u0142ego BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of the White Eagle (Poland)]] [[File:POL Polonia Restituta Wielki BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of Polonia Restituta]] [[File:POR Ordem do Merito Gra-Cruz BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of Merit (Portugal)]] [[File:Grand_Crest_Ordre_de_Leopold.png|40px|link=Order of Leopold (Belgium)]] [[File:CZE_Rad_Bileho_Lva_1_tridy_BAR.svg|40px|link=Order of White Lion (Czech Republic)]] [[File:Order Stara planina ribbon.png|40px|link=Order of Stara Planina (Bulgaria)]] [[File:St Olavs Orden storkors stripe.svg|40px|link=Order of St. Olav]] [[File:Star of Romania Ribbon.PNG|40px|link=Order of the Star of Romania]] [[File:FIN Order of the White Rose Grand Cross BAR.png|40px|link=Order of the White Rose of Finland]] [[File:GRE Order Redeemer 1Class.png|40px|link=Order of the Redeemer]] [[File:LVA Order of the Three Stars - Commander BAR.png|40px|link=Order of the Three Stars]] [[File:LTU Order of Vytautas the Great with the Golden Chain BAR.png|40px]] [[File:SVK Rad Bieleho Dvojkriza 1 triedy BAR.svg|40px]]\n| honorific_suffix = \n}}\n'''Andrzej Sebastian Duda''' ({{small|Polish pronunciation:}} {{IPAc-pl|AUD|Pl-Andrzej_Duda.ogg|\u02c8|a|n|d|\u0290|\u025b|j|-|\u02c8|d|u|d|a}}; born 16 May 1972) is a [[Poles|Polish]] lawyer and politician who serves as the current [[List of heads of state of Poland#Republic of Poland (1989\u2013present)|President of Poland]], holding the office since 6 August 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/05/24/andrzej-duda-elected-president-poland_n_7432554.html|title=Andrzej Duda Elected Poland's New President, Incumbent Bronislaw Komorowski Concedes Defeat|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=25 May 2015}}</ref> Before his tenure as President, Duda was a member of Polish Lower House ([[Sejm]]) from 2011 to 2014 and the [[European Parliament]] from 2014 to 2015.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mularczyk|first1=Arkadiusz|title=Lista kandydat\u00f3w na zast\u0119pc\u00f3w przewodnicz\u0105cego i cz\u0142onk\u00f3w Trybuna\u0142u Stanu|url=http://orka.sejm.gov.pl/Druki6ka.nsf/0/1A8000B1E3780FA8C125738C00554FC5/$file/3.pdf|website=Sejm of the Republic of Poland|publisher=|accessdate=31 January 2015|language=pl}}</ref>\n\nDuda was the presidential candidate for the [[right wing]] [[Law and Justice]] party, during the [[2015 Polish presidential election|2015 presidential election]] in May 2015. In the first round of voting, Duda received 5,179,092 votes \u2013 34.76% of valid votes. In the second round of voting, Duda received 51.55% of the vote, beating the incumbent president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]], who received 48.45% of the vote. On 26 May 2015, Duda resigned his party membership as the president-elect. On October 24, 2019 he received the official support from PiS ahead of his re-election campaign in [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]].\n\n== Early life ==\nDuda was born in [[Krak\u00f3w]], to Janina Milewska and Jan Tadeusz Duda, professors at the [[AGH University of Science and Technology]]. His grandfather fought in the [[Polish\u2013Soviet War]] and later was a member of the [[Home Army (Poland)|Home Army]] during the [[Second World War]].<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\">{{cite news|title=Duda story \u2013 historia mi\u0142o\u015bci, podboju g\u00f3r i niespodziewanego wej\u015bcia w polityk\u0119|url=http://niezalezna.pl/64196-duda-story-historia-milosci-podboju-gor-i-niespodziewanego-wejscia-w-polityke|accessdate=30 May 2015|date=14 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nDuda attended [[Jan III Sobieski High School, Krak\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Rodzina Dud\u00f3w: nowy prezydent jest zapalonym narciarzem i molem ksi\u0105\u017ckowym. Jego \u017cona to wymagaj\u0105ca nauczycielka|url=http://www.tvp.info/20194423/rodzina-dudow-nowy-prezydent-jest-zapalonym-narciarzem-i-molem-ksiazkowym-jego-zona-to-wymagajaca-nauczycielka|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=TVP}}</ref> He subsequently studied law at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. In October 2001 he was appointed as an assistant (holding M.A.) in the Administrative Law Department of Jagiellonian University. In January 2005, Duda also obtained a [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] degree in law at the [[Jagiellonian University]]. Due to his political career, he has been mostly on unpaid leave (from the university) since September 2006, except for a 13-month interval beginning in September 2010, when he returned to the university.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andrzej Duda od blisko 9 lat jest na urlopie bezp\u0142atnym z UJ|url=http://www.rmf24.pl/raport-wybory-prezydenckie2015/najnowsze-fakty/news-andrzej-duda-od-blisko-9-lat-jest-na-urlopie-bezplatnym-z-uj,nId,1735152|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=RMF FM|date=18 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Political career ==\n[[File:Andrzej Duda Lech Kaczynski.jpg|thumb|left|Former President [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]] appointing Duda as undersecretary of state in the Chancellery of the President, 16 January 2008]]\nDuda began his political career with the now-defunct [[Freedom Union (Poland)|Freedom Union]] Party in the early 2000s. After the parliamentary elections in 2005, he began his collaboration with the [[Law and Justice]] Party (PiS).<ref name=\"Micha\u0142 Krzymowski Anna Szulc2015\">{{cite web |url=http://polska.newsweek.pl/andrzej-duda-byl-dzialaczem-unii-wolnosci,artykuly,359002,1.html#fp=nw |author=Micha\u0142 Krzymowski, Anna Szulc |title=Andrzej Duda by\u0142 dzia\u0142aczem Unii Wolno\u015bci |website=newsweek.pl |date=14 March 2015 |access-date=14 March 2015 |language=Polish |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150423090718/http://polska.newsweek.pl/andrzej-duda-byl-dzialaczem-unii-wolnosci,artykuly,359002,1.html#fp=nw |archive-date=23 April 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> From 2006 to 2007, Andrzej Duda was an undersecretary of state in the [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Ministry of Justice]]. Then, from 2007 to 2008, Duda was a member of the [[Polish State Tribunal]].\n\nFrom 2008 to 2010, during the presidency of [[Lech Kaczy\u0144ski]], Duda was an undersecretary of state in the [[Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.andrzejduda.pl/o-mnie |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150526110639/http://m.andrzejduda.pl/o-mnie |url-status=dead |archive-date=26 May 2015 |title=Andrzej Duda |work=andrzejduda.pl }}</ref> In 2010, he was an unsuccessful candidate to become the Mayor of Krak\u00f3w as a PiS candidate,<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2010\">{{cite web |url = http://wybory2010.pkw.gov.pl/geo/pl/120000/126101.html#tabs-4 |title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2010 |access-date=24 November 2010|language=Polish}}</ref> but was more successful in the 2011 parliamentary election, where he received 79,981 votes for the Krak\u00f3w area, and thus became member of the [[Sejm]].<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2011\">{{cite web |url = http://wybory2011.pkw.gov.pl/wsw/pl/sjm-13.html |title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2011 |access-date=28 October 2011|language=Polish}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, the [[news magazine]] ''[[Polityka]]'' commended Duda for being one of the most active members of parliament, at the time, describing him as being open to opposition arguments and as refraining from personal attacks, as part of his role at the Commission for Constitutional Responsibility.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Paradowska|first1=Janina|last2=D\u0105browska|first2=Anna|title=Pos\u0142owie na medal i pos\u0142owie z nagan\u0105|url=http://www.polityka.pl/tygodnikpolityka/kraj/1556381,1,ranking-poslow-polityki-rozstrzygniety.read|accessdate=26 May 2015|agency=Polityka|date=26 September 2013}}</ref> Duda remained a member of the Sejm until he was elected to the [[European Parliament]] in 2014.<ref name=\"Serwis PKW Wybory 2014\">{{cite web|url=http://pe2014.pkw.gov.pl/pl/|title=Serwis PKW \u2013 Wybory 2014|access-date=27 May 2014|language=Polish|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140824100453/http://pe2014.pkw.gov.pl/pl/|archive-date=24 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015 Presidential Campaign ===\n{{main|2015 Polish presidential election}}\nIn the shade of the upcoming expiration of president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]'s first term, Komorowski was able to seek re-election in a scheduled presidential election. Duda was Komorowski's [[Law and Justice]] rival in the election.\n\nIn the first round of the [[2015 Polish presidential election|2015 presidential election]], Duda came first, receiving 5,179,092 votes and thus 34.76% of valid votes.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://prezydent2015.pkw.gov.pl/pliki/1_Obwieszczenie.pdf |title=Obwieszczenie Pa\u0144stwowej Komisji Wyborczej z dnia 11 maja 2015 r. o wynikach g\u0142osowania i wyniku wybor\u00f3w Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej, zarz\u0105dzonych na dzie\u0144 10 maja 2015 r. |access-date=12 May 2015 |website=pkw.gov.pl|language=Polish}}</ref>\n\nIn the second round Duda took 51.55% of the vote against the 48.45% share of his rival, then-incumbent president [[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prezydent2015.pkw.gov.pl/325_Ponowne_glosowanie|title=PKW \u2013 www.prezydent.2015.pkw.gov.pl|work=pkw.gov.pl}}</ref> On 26 May 2015, he officially resigned from party membership.<ref>{{cite news|title=Andrzej Duda ju\u017c poza PiS. Zrzek\u0142 si\u0119 cz\u0142onkostwa|url=http://www.tvp.info/20215021/andrzej-duda-juz-poza-pis-zrzekl-sie-czlonkostwa|accessdate=26 May 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Presidency ==\n[[File:Andrzej Duda Bogdan Borusewicz Ma\u0142gorzata Kidawa-B\u0142o\u0144ska Zgromadzenie Narodowe 6 sierpnia 2015 01.JPG|thumb|Andrzej Duda taking the oath of office, 6 August 2015]]\n[[File:Wsp\u00f3lne o\u015bwiadczenie w sprawie ustanowienia wszechstronnego strategicznego partnerstwa.jpg|thumb|Duda and [[Xi Jinping]] signed a declaration on strategic partnership]]\n[[File:President Trump's Trip to Poland (34920988424) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Duda and his wife Agata Kornhauser-Duda with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and [[Melania Trump]] in Warsaw]]\nThe five-year term of Andrzej Duda began on 6 August 2015 with taking an oath of office during a [[National Assembly (Poland)|National Assembly]] session.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,5,uroczystosci-inauguracji-prezydenta-rp-andrzeja-dudy.html|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150806134223/http://prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,5,uroczystosci-inauguracji-prezydenta-rp-andrzeja-dudy.html|url-status=dead|title=Oficjalna strona Prezydenta Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej / Aktualno\u015bci /\u2026|date=6 August 2015|archivedate=6 August 2015|website=archive.is|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nDuda rejected the [[European Union]]'s proposal of [[European migrant crisis#Relocation and resettlement of asylum seekers|migrant quotas to redistribute asylum seekers]], saying: \"I won\u2019t agree to a dictate of the strong. I won\u2019t back a Europe where the economic advantage of the size of a population will be a reason to force solutions on other countries regardless of their national interests\".<ref>\"[https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-09-08/polish-president-blasts-eu-dictate-of-the-strong-on-migrants Poland's Duda Blasts EU `Dictate of the Strong' on Migrants]\". ''Bloomberg.'' 8 September 2015.</ref>\n\nEventually former Prime Minister [[Ewa Kopacz]] declared that Poland, as an expression of \u201cEuropean solidarity\u201d, would take in 2,000 people over the next two years, mainly from Syria and Eritrea (out of 3,700 originally requested).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/10/opinion/poland-shouldnt-shut-out-refugees.html|title=Opinion - Poland Shouldn\u2019t Shut Out Refugees|first=Konstanty|last=Gebert|date=9 September 2015|publisher=|access-date=6 February 2018|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref>\n\nDuda and Croatian President [[Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovi\u0107]] were the originators of the [[Three Seas Initiative]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvn24.pl/magazyn-tvn24/wielki-plan-malych-panstw-jak-trojmorze-wzmocni-lub-podzieli-unie,106,1968|title=Wielki plan ma\u0142ych pa\u0144stw. Jak Tr\u00f3jmorze wzmocni lub podzieli Uni\u0119|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nDuda repeatedly met with [[General Secretary of the Communist Party of China|general secretary]] of the [[Communist Party of China]] and China's leader, [[Xi Jinping]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Xi Jinping Holds Talks with President Andrzej Duda of Poland, Two Heads of State Decide to Promote Development Level of China-Poland Strategic Partnership |url=http://www.chinaembassy.se/eng/wjdt/t1319025.htm |work=Chinaembassy.se |date=25 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=President Duda sends sympathy message to President Xi Jinping |url=https://www.thefirstnews.com/article/president-duda-sends-sympathy-message-to-president-xi-jinping-10277 |work=Polish Press Agency |date=3 February 2020}}</ref> stating that \"Polish companies will benefit hugely\" from China's [[Belt and Road Initiative]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Polish president says Xi Jinping understands central European dynamic |url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/world/2016xivisitee/2016-06/19/content_25763414.htm |work=Chinadaily.com.cn |date=19 June 2016}}</ref> Duda and Xi signed a declaration on [[strategic partnership]] in which they reiterated that Poland and China viewed each other as long-term strategic partners.<ref>{{cite news |title=Xi welcomes Chinese freight train to 'strategic partner' Poland |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-poland-china-xi/xi-welcomes-chinese-freight-train-to-strategic-partner-poland-idUKKCN0Z6205 |agency=Reuters |date=20 June 2016}}</ref> Duda said that he hope Poland will become a gateway to Europe for China.<ref>{{cite news |title=Poland and China sign universal strategic partnership pact |url=http://archiwum.thenews.pl/1/10/Artykul/257974,Poland-and-China-sign-universal-strategic-partnership-pact |work=Radio Poland |date=20 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, his approval rating stood at 71% and in February 2018, at 72%, a record surpassed only by [[Aleksander Kwa\u015bniewski]], whose approval ratings surpassed 75% from 1995 to 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dorzeczy.pl/kraj/40293/Sondaz-CBOS-Wielki-wzrost-poparcia-dla-prezydenta-Dudy.html|title=Sonda\u017c CBOS: Wielki wzrost poparcia dla prezydenta Dudy|trans-title=|language=|website=dorzeczy.pl|access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polityka/cbos-prezydent-duda-z-najwiekszym-poparciem-premier-morawiecki-na-drugim-miejscu/lr073kx|title=Prezydent Duda z najwi\u0119kszym poparciem|trans-title=|language=|website=fakt.pl|access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism and controversies ===\nIn November 2015, basing on Art. 139 of the [[Constitution of Poland]], Duda pardoned former [[Central Anticorruption Bureau]] (CBA) head [[Mariusz Kami\u0144ski]] and three CBA officers convicted by a court of 1st instance in the so-called \"[[:pl:Afera gruntowa|Land Affair]]\",<ref>\"[http://www.pap.pl/aktualnosci/news,432779,prezydent-ulaskawil-min-b-szefa-cba-mariusza-kaminskiego.html]\". ''Polska Agencja Prasowa'', 17 November 2015.</ref> marking the first pardon granted by a president before reaching a final verdict.<ref>Marek Domagalski. Prezydencka \u0142aska dzieli prawnik\u00f3w. ''Rzeczpospolita'', p. C2, 19 November 2015.</ref> According to some lawyers (including professors Jan Zimmermann \u2013 Andrzej Duda's doctorate promoter, Leszek Kubicki \u2013 former [[Ministry of Justice (Poland)|Minister of Justice]] and [[Andrzej Zoll]] \u2013 former president of the [[Constitutional Tribunal (Poland)|Constitutional Tribunal]]) Duda breached the Constitution of Poland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/opinie/artykuly/507262,prof-jan-zimmermann-z-uj-prezydent-andrzej-duda-zlamal-konstytucje-trzykrotnie.html|title=\"Prezydent z\u0142ama\u0142 konstytucj\u0119 przynajmniej trzykrotnie\". Promotor Andrzeja Dudy krytykuje swojego doktoranta|author=|date=|website=wiadomosci.dziennik.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref><ref>[http://wyborcza.pl/1,75478,19210341,czy-prezydent-zlamal-konstytucje-prawnicy-podzieleni.html Ewa Siedlecka, ''Wyborcza.pl'', 18 November 2015]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://polskatimes.pl/prof-andrzej-zoll-prezydent-duda-zlamal-prawo/ar/9099824|title=Prof. Andrzej Zoll: Prezydent Duda z\u0142ama\u0142 prawo|first=Maria|last=Mazurek|date=19 November 2015|website=polskatimes.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAndrzej Duda has refused to [[Oath of office|swear in]] any of the five [[Constitutional Tribunal (Poland)|Constitutional Tribunal]] judge candidates selected by the [[Sejm]] of the VII term. Three of those were selected since 7 November 2015 whose election was declared constitutional.<ref>\"[http://isap.sejm.gov.pl/DetailsServlet?id=WDU20150002129]\". ''Dziennik Ustaw'' from 2015, pos. 2129</ref> On 3 and 9 December 2015 Duda swore in five other candidates for the same office selected by the Sejm of the VIII term.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20151203124052/http://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art%2C75%2Cprezydent-odebral-slubowanie-od-sedziow-tk.html]\". prezydent.pl, 3 December 2015</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,80,prezydent-przyjal-slubowanie-od-sedzi-tk-julii-przylebskiej.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226082006/https://www.prezydent.pl/aktualnosci/wydarzenia/art,80,prezydent-przyjal-slubowanie-od-sedzi-tk-julii-przylebskiej.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=26 December 2015|title=prezydent.pl, 9 December 2015|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 December 2015, Duda signed the Constitutional Tribunal bill (passed on 22 December 2015 by the Sejm), which unequivocally breaches the Constitution of Poland according to the National Council of the Judiciary of Poland,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.krs.pl/pl/aktualnosci/d,2015,12/3872,stanowisko-prezydium-krajowej-rady-sadownictwa-w-sprawie-uchwalonej-22-grudnia-2015-r-zmiany-ustawy-o-trybunale-konstytucyjnym-dz-u-poz-1064-ze-zm|title=Aktualno\u015bci - Stanowisko Prezydium Krajowej Rady S\u0105downictwa w sprawie uchwalonej 22 grudnia 2015 r. zmiany ustawy o Trybunale Konstytucyjnym (Dz. U. poz. 1064 ze zm.) - Krajowa Rada S\u0105downictwa|author=|date=|website=www.krs.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref> the [[Public Prosecutor General (Poland)|Public Prosecutor General]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.dziennik.pl/polityka/artykuly/508968,prokurator-generalny-o-nowelizacji-ustawy-o-trybunale-konstytucyjnym.html|title=Nowelizacja ustawy o TK. Prokurator Generalny straszy parali\u017cem prac|author=|date=|website=wiadomosci.dziennik.pl|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref> and the [[Polish Ombudsman]].<ref>[http://www.rp.pl/Sedziowie-i-sady/312249956-RPO-i-HFPC-apeluja--do-prezydenta-ws-noweli-ustawy-o-TK.html] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180102013150/http://www.rp.pl/Sedziowie-i-sady/312249956-RPO-i-HFPC-apeluja--do-prezydenta-ws-noweli-ustawy-o-TK.html |date=2 January 2018 }}, rp.pl, 24 December 2015</ref>\n\nIn June 2016, Duda rejected appointing 10 judges selected by the National Council of the Judiciary of Poland.<ref>Ewa Siedlecka, \"Prezydent s\u0105dzi s\u0119dzi\u00f3w\", ''[[Gazeta Wyborcza]]'', p. 1, 29 June 2016</ref><!-- this does not explain how it is either a criticism or controversy -->\n\nIn July 2017, Duda informed the public he had decided to veto two controversial judicial bills backed by the government and passed by both houses of the Polish parliament. The President's spokesman subsequently said that the third act \u2013 the common courts bill \u2013 would be signed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.president.pl/en/news/art,508,president-to-veto-two-judicial-bills-says-will-sign-bill-on-common-courts.html|title=President of the Republic of Poland / News / President to veto two judicial bills, says will sign bill on common courts|website=www.president.pl|accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref> The veto was just one example of Duda opposing the policies of PiS.<ref name=\"veconomist\" >{{cite news|author=|title=Poland\u2019s president turns on his former boss|url=https://www.economist.com/news/europe/21730165-ruling-law-and-justice-partys-plan-nobble-polish-institutions-hits-roadblock-polands|work=[[The Economist]]|date=12 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, Duda said that he would sign into law [[Amendment to the Act on the Institute of National Remembrance|the \"Holocaust bill\"]], making it illegal to accuse 'the Polish nation' of complicity in the Holocaust and other Nazi atrocities, a measure that has roiled relations with Israel and the United States, with Prime Minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]] going as far as accusing the Polish government of [[Holocaust denial]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/worldviews/wp/2018/01/27/it-could-soon-be-a-crime-to-blame-poland-for-nazi-atrocities-and-israel-is-appalled/|title=Analysis {{!}} It could soon be a crime to blame Poland for Nazi atrocities, and Israel is appalled|last=Selk|first=Avi|date=27 January 2018|work=Washington Post|access-date=28 January 2018|language=en-US|issn=0190-8286}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/06/world/europe/poland-holocaust-law.html|title=Poland\u2019s President Supports Making Some Holocaust Statements a Crime|first=Marc|last=Santora|date=6 February 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-israel-poland/polands-president-duda-says-will-sign-holocaust-bill-into-law-idUSKBN1FQ1EQ|title=Polish president signs Holocaust bill, triggers Israeli, U.S. criticism|first=Pawel|last=Sobczak|date=6 February 2018|work=Reuters|access-date=9 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nDuda is married to [[Agata Kornhauser-Duda]], a teacher of [[German language|German]] language at Jan III Sobieski High School in Krak\u00f3w.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teachers|url=http://www.sobieski.krakow.pl/o-szkole/nauczyciele/}}</ref> They had met at a party while still attending rival schools<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\"/> and have been married since 21 December 1994.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wantuch|first1=Dominika|title=Agata Kornhauser-Duda. Pierwsza Dama w stylu zachodnim|url=http://krakow.gazeta.pl/krakow/1,44425,17983045,Agata_Kornhauser_Duda__Pierwsza_Dama_w_stylu_zachodnim.html|accessdate=28 May 2015|agency=Gazeta Wyborcza|date=25 May 2015}}</ref> Together they have one daughter, Kinga, born in 1995, who also graduated in law in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Andrzej Duda opublikowa\u0142 zdj\u0119cie c\u00f3rki na Instagramie. Pochwali\u0142 si\u0119 jej sukcesem |url=https://natemat.pl/272777,kinga-duda-skonczyla-studia-andrzej-duda-pochwalil-sie-na-instagramie |website=naTemat.pl |accessdate=25 May 2019 |language=pl}}</ref> His father-in-law is [[Julian Kornhauser]], a well-known writer, translator and literary critic.<ref>Marek Bartosik, [http://www.gazetakrakowska.pl/artykul/334041,andrzej-duda-spozniony-pociag-do-polityki,id,t.html Andrzej Duda: sp\u00f3\u017aniony poci\u0105g do polityki] Gazeta Krakowska 19 November 2010 {{in lang|pl}}</ref>\n\nHe is a keen skier and while studying participated in the Polish Academic Championships in the [[Alpine skiing]] category.<ref name=\"niezalezna.pl\"/>\n\nDuda is a Catholic. He took part in religious ceremonies on many occasions, including [[Midnight Mass]], the [[\u015awi\u0119conka|blessing of food]] on [[Holy Saturday]], or the [[Corpus Christi procession]] in [[Krak\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.se.pl/wiadomosci/polityka/prezydent-andrzej-duda-z-rodzina-na-pasterce-zdjecia_755537.html |title=Prezydent Andrzej Duda z rodzin\u0105 na pasterce [ZDJ\u0118CIA] |publisher=Super Express |work=katk |date=27 December 2015 |accessdate=21 April 2016 |language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fakt.pl/politycy/andrzej-duda-i-kinga-duda-w-kosciele-ze-swieconka,galeria,621054.html |title=Andrzej Duda z c\u00f3rk\u0105 \u015bwi\u0119ci jajeczko |publisher=Fakt |work=js |date=26 March 2016 |accessdate=21 April 2016 |language=pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://natemat.pl/151749,prezydent-i-koscioly-od-wyborow-andrzej-duda-ma-wiecej-zdjec-ze-mszy-niz-z-panstwowych-uroczystosci |title=Prezydent i ko\u015bcio\u0142y. Od wybor\u00f3w Andrzej Duda ma wi\u0119cej zdj\u0119\u0107 ze mszy ni\u017c z pa\u0144stwowych uroczysto\u015bci |publisher=natemat.pl |last=Sikora |first=Kamil |date=17 August 2015 |accessdate=21 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Honours ==\n=== National Honours===\n* {{flag|Poland}}: [[Order of the White Eagle (Poland)|Order of the White Eagle]] (''[[ex officio]]'')\n* {{flag|Poland}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of Polonia Restituta]] (''ex officio'')\n\n===Foreign Honours===\n* {{flag|Belgium}}: Gran Cordon of the [[Order of Leopold (Belgium)|Order of Leopold]] (2015)\n* {{flag|Bulgaria}}: I Class [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Bulgaria#Orders 4|Order of Stara Planina]] (\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430) (14 April 2016)<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.lex.bg/bg/laws/ldoc/2136801460 |title=\u0423\u043a\u0430\u0437 \u2116 99 \u043e\u0442 14.04.2016 \u0433. \u0417\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u0433-\u043d \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0439 \u0414\u0443\u0434\u0430 \u2013 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0420\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0431\u043b\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u041f\u043e\u043b\u0448\u0430, \u0441 \u043e\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \"\u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430\" \u0441 \u043b\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 |access-date=3 May 2016 |website=lex.bg |language=bg}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Czech Republic}}: Collar of the [[Order of the White Lion]] (15 March 2016)\n* {{flag|Finland}}: Grand Cross with Collar [[Order of the White Rose of Finland]] (2017)\n* {{flag|Greece}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Redeemer]] (2017)\n* {{flag|Latvia}}: Commander Grand Cross with Chain of the [[Order of the Three Stars]] (2018)\n* {{flag|Lithuania}}: Grand Cross with Golden Chain of the [[Order of Vytautas the Great]] (21 February 2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lrp.lt/en/|title=President of the Republic of Lithuania|author=|date=|website=www.lrp.lt|access-date=29 April 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Norway}}: Grand Cross of the Royal Norwegian [[Order of St. Olav]] (23 May 2016)\n* {{flag|Portugal}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of Merit (Portugal)|Order of Merit Grand Cross]] (2008)<ref>{{cite web |url = http://dre.pt/pdf2sdip/2009/02/040000000/0769107691.pdf |title=Chancelaria das Ordens Honor\u00edficas Portuguesas |access-date=12 September 2010 |website=dre.pt |language=pt}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Romania}}: Collar of the [[Order of the Star of Romania]] (10 July 2016)\n* {{flag|Slovakia}}: Grand Cross of the [[Order of the White Double Cross]] (2019)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons}}\n{{Portal|Poland|Biography}}\n* [http://www.president.pl/en/president/biography Official Biography of President Andrzej Duda]\n* [http://www.president.pl/en/ The official website of the President of the Republic of Poland]\n* [http://www.sejm.gov.pl/english.html Polish Sejm]\n* [http://ludzie.wprost.pl/sylwetka/4102128/Andrzej-Duda.html Wprost] {{in lang|pl}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bronis\u0142aw Komorowski]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of Poland]]|years=2015\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jaros\u0142aw Kaczy\u0144ski]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Law and Justice]] nominee for <br /> [[President of Poland]]|years=[[2015 Polish presidential election|2015]] and [[2020 Polish presidential election|2020]]}}\n{{s-inc|recent}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|poland}}\n{{s-new|first}}\